# Approach
Define a helper function solve that takes the matrix, current indices (i and j), the reference to maxi, and the dp matrix as parameters.

Inside the solve function, check if the indices i and j are out of bounds of the matrix. If they are, return 0.

Check if the current cell in the matrix is already visited (marked by dp[i][j] != -1). If it is, return the value stored in dp[i][j].

Recursively call the solve function for the right cell, diagonal cell, and bottom cell to explore all possible squares starting from the current position. Store the results in right, diagonal, and bottom variables.

If the current cell contains a '1', calculate the size of the square that can be formed starting from this cell. This can be done by adding 1 to the minimum of the values from the right, diagonal, and bottom cells.

Update maxi by taking the maximum of the current square size and the existing maxi.

Store the current square size in dp[i][j] for memoization.

Return the current square size.

In the maximalSquare function, initialize the dp matrix with -1 values.

Initialize maxi with 0 before calling the solve function with the starting indices (0, 0) and the matrix.

Return the maximum square area by multiplying maxi by itself (i.e., maxi * maxi).

This approach uses dynamic programming and memoization to avoid redundant calculations and optimize the solution.
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->



# Code
```
#include <algorithm>
#include <vector>
class Solution {
public:
int solve(vector<vector<char>>& matrix, int i , int j ,int& maxi,vector<vector<int>>&dp)
{
    // CHECK IF INDEX ARE OUT OF BOUND OR NOT 
    if(i>=matrix.size() || j>=matrix[0].size())
    {
        return 0 ;
    }

    if(dp[i][j]!=-1)
    {
        return dp[i][j];
    }
    int right=solve(matrix,i,j+1,maxi,dp);
    int diagonal=solve(matrix,i+1,j+1,maxi,dp);
    int bottom=solve(matrix,i+1,j,maxi,dp);
    if(matrix[i][j]=='1')
    {
        dp[i][j] = 1+min(right, min(diagonal , bottom));
        maxi=max(dp[i][j],maxi);
        return dp[i][j];
    }
    else
        return 0 ;

}
    int maximalSquare(vector<vector<char>>& matrix)
    {
        int n = matrix.size();
        int m = matrix[0].size();
        vector<vector<int>>dp(n,vector<int>(m,-1));

        int maxi = 0;
        int s=solve(matrix, 0,0 , maxi,dp);
          return maxi * maxi; 
    }
};
```

