**Idea**
* **Dynamic Programming**
* `dp[i][j] = 1 + min({dp[i][j-1],dp[i-1][j],dp[i-1][j-1]})` when `matrix[i][j]` contains '1'
* We can optimise the above n * m dp table to 2 * m dp table since answering for current cell (r,c) depends totally on current and previous row.

```
class Solution {
public:
    // Time Complexity:- O(NM)
    // Space Complexity:- O(M)
    int maximalSquare(vector<vector<char>>& matrix) {
        int side = 0;
        vector<vector<int>> dp(2,vector<int>(matrix[0].size()));
        for(int i=0;i<matrix.size();i++){
            for(int j=0;j<matrix[i].size();j++){
                dp[i%2][j] = matrix[i][j]-'0';
                if(i and j and dp[i%2][j])
                    dp[i%2][j] = 1 + min({dp[i%2][j-1],dp[(i-1)%2][j],dp[(i-1)%2][j-1]});
                side = max(side,dp[i%2][j]);
            }
        }
        return side*side;
    }
};
```
