This solution is based on [Maximal Rectangle](https://leetcode.com/problems/maximal-rectangle/) The solution is not the best for this  problem, though. However, this solution is the proof-of-concept that we can move from the problem "finding the maximum rectangle" into the "finding the maximum square".

**Main idea:** The whole point of finding the maxium rectangle algorithm is: we try to find the pair (W,  H) that can be formed the rectangle that we cannot stretch anymore on either side. Other word, there is no another pair(W1, H) that W1 > W and (W1,H) also a rectangle. Similarity for (W, H1). Because of that, **the maximum square must be inside one of the rectangle we have founed**

So from the formula:
```
 max = Math.max(max, h[top] * (right-left+1));
```

We can get the minimum of both sides before calculating the area.
```
 int side = Math.min(h[top], right-left+1);
 max = Math.max(max, side*side);
```

Time complexity: O(N*M)
Space complexity: O(M)

```
class Solution {
    public int maximalSquare(char[][] matrix) {
        int n = matrix.length;
        if (n == 0) return 0;
        int m = matrix[0].length;

        int[] h  =  new int[m];
        int max = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int  j = 0; j < m; j++) {
                if (matrix[i][j] == '0') h[j] = 0;
                else h[j] = h[j]+1;
            }
            max = Math.max(max, maxArea(h));
        }
        return max;
    }

    // find the  maximum area of this histogram
    private int maxArea(int[] h)  {
        Stack<Integer> stack = new Stack<Integer>();
        int n = h.length;
        int max = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            while (!stack.isEmpty() && h[stack.peek()] > h[i]) {
                int top = stack.pop();
                int right = i-1;
                int left = stack.isEmpty() ? 0 : stack.peek()+1;
                int range = right-left+1;
                int side = Math.min(h[top], right-left+1);
                max = Math.max(max, side*side);
            }
            stack.push(i);
        }

        if (!stack.isEmpty()) {
            int pivot = stack.peek();
            while (!stack.isEmpty()) {
                int top = stack.pop();
                int right = pivot;
                int left = stack.isEmpty() ? 0 : stack.peek()+1;
                int range = right-left+1;
                int side = Math.min(h[top], right-left+1);
                max =  Math.max(max, side*side);
            }
        }

        return max;
    }
}
```

