3. **T**urn the top-down solution upside-down to create the bottom-up solution

Only consider cells with value `'1'` as candidate participants in a maximal square.

**Top-Down recurrence relation:** The optimal solution for each cell is 1 + the minimum of the adjacent cells down, right, down-and-right

**Bottom-Up recurrence relation:** The optimal solution for each cell is 1 + the minimum of the adjacent cells above, left, above-and-left

