**Problem**. Given an m x n binary matrix filled with 0's and 1's, find the largest square containing only 1's and return its area. 
This problem can be elegantly solved with a **dp strategy**.

```
class Solution {
    public int maximalSquare(char[][] matrix) {
        int[][] dp = new int[matrix.length][matrix[0].length];
        int ans = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i < matrix.length; i++){
            for(int j = 0; j < matrix[0].length; j ++){
                if(matrix[i][j] == '1'){
                   //initialization
				   if(i == 0|| j == 0)
                        dp[i][j] = 1;
                     else 
                        dp[i][j] = Math.min(Math.min(dp[i - 1][j - 1], dp[i - 1][j]), dp[i][j - 1]) + 1;

                    ans = Math.max(ans, dp[i][j] * dp[i][j]);
                }
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
```
**TC: O(mn)
TS: O(mn)**

Now we implement a space optimized solution. We apply the same logic.
Instead of using a dp **m**x**n** matrix, we use only an array, that represent each column, and a int value, right_up, that is the fourth value needed to populate the dp array (one is matrix[i][i], then dp[i], dp[i-1] and right_up, that is the old dp[i-1], of the previus column).


![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/d9209d70-b067-49ea-88a1-92eb622cf218_1639843295.2600548.jpeg)
I hope I was helpful, if yes then upvote. Thanks.
**Given m rows and n columns**
**TC: O(mn)
TS: O(m+1)= O(m)**

```
class Solution {
    public int maximalSquare(char[][] matrix) {

         /*
                        dp[i-1][j-1]  ||  dp[i-1] [j]
                   ----------------------------------
                        dp[i][j-1]     ||   dp[i][j]
                    */

        int[] dp = new int[matrix.length]; //rows
        int ans = 0;

        int up_right = 0;

        for(int j = 0; j < matrix[0].length; j++)
            for(int i = 0; i < matrix.length; i++)

            {
                    if(i == 0 || j == 0  || matrix[i][j] -'0' == 0)
                    {
                        if(matrix[i][j]-'0' == 1 && ans==0)
                           ans = 1;

                        if(j >= 1)
                            up_right = dp[i];

                            dp[i] = matrix[i][j] - '0';

                    }

                     else 

                         if(matrix[i][j]-'0'== 1)
                         {
                             int store= dp[i];
                             dp[i] = Math.min(Math.min(dp[i], dp[i - 1]), up_right) + 1;
                             up_right = store;
                             ans = Math.max(ans, dp[i]);

                         }

                }


        return ans*ans;
    }
}
```

