Logic : 
1. We traverse the array normally and keep track of the largest side length of the square we can form at `dp[i][j]`
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/e6b1c939-4bcf-4991-873b-8530f4feeac9_1629375252.2617404.png)

If any of the `1s` would have been 0 then the square of 2*2 would not have been possible . And this is checked via the `min of all the 3 blocks +1` 

Similary for 3*3 it would have been something like this 
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/2a3dc777-21c1-46f0-a4c5-2228beff5fe8_1629375565.619509.png)


```
int maximalSquare(vector<vector<char>>& matrix) {
        int m= matrix.size() , n=matrix[0].size();
       vector<vector<int>>dp(m,vector<int>(n,0));
        int res=0;
        for(int i=0 ; i<m ;i++){

            for(int j=0 ;j<n ;j++){

                if(matrix[i][j]=='1'){

                    if(i==0 || j==0)  // If Bounday elements then max is 1
                    dp[i][j]=1;
                else
                    dp[i][j]=1+ min({dp[i-1][j] , dp[i][j-1] , dp[i-1][j-1]});   // This conditon is to check whether all the rest are valid or not 
                }

                res=max(res,dp[i][j]);
            }
        }

        return pow(res,2);
    }
